Read second time: March 4, 2026
CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Talbot County – Public Schools – School Schedule Options
3 FOR the purpose of authorizing the Talbot County Board of Education to operate schools
4 within the county using a certain school scheduling model that is exempt from a
5 certain requirement under certain circumstances; requiring a school operating under
6 a certain scheduling model to provide the county board to offer certain employees an
7 opportunity to make up lost wages under certain circumstances; and generally
8 relating to public school scheduling models and the Talbot County Board of
9 Education.
10 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
11 Article – Education
12 Section 7–103(a)
13 Annotated Code of Maryland
14 (2025 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
15 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
16 Article – Education
17 Section 7–103(f)
18 Annotated Code of Maryland
19 (2025 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
20 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
21 Article – Education
22 Section 7–103(a), (f), and (g)
